==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Capitate
<hw>Cap"i*tate</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧p"⟦icr⟧*t⟦asl⟧t)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>capitatus</ets> fr. <ets>caput</ets> head.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Headlike in form; also, having the distal end enlarged
and rounded, as the stigmas of certain flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the flowers gathered into a
head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>capitatim</ent>⟦br⟧
